# Jobs Component

Scheduled Prometheus metric collectors that gather execution layer metrics via periodic RPC calls to Ethereum nodes.

## Key Patterns
- **Periodic Collection**: All jobs use consistent tick-based pattern with time.After() intervals (5-15 seconds)
- **Module-Based Structure**: Each job corresponds to specific Ethereum RPC modules (admin, net, txpool, web3, eth)
- **Error Resilience**: Jobs continue operating despite individual RPC failures, logging errors without stopping collection
- **Modular Registration**: Jobs only register when required RPC modules are enabled via ExporterCanRun()

## Implementation Constraints  
- All job structs must embed same client dependencies (ethclient, api.ExecutionClient, ethrpc.EthRPC)
- Use consistent Prometheus metric naming: namespace + "_" + module + "_" + metric_name
- Implement context-based cancellation in Start() methods for graceful shutdown
- Include "module" label in constLabels for metric identification